sql:
SELECT chromosome, position
FROM variant_records
WHERE chromosome = '1';

SELECT file_name, COUNT(*) AS file_count
FROM vcf_files
GROUP BY file_name;

SELECT file_name, upload_date
FROM vcf_files
WHERE file_id = 1;

SELECT COUNT(*) AS file_count
FROM vcf_files
WHERE user_id = 1001;

SELECT file_name, user_id
FROM vcf_files
WHERE upload_date = (SELECT MAX(upload_date) FROM vcf_files);

external_knowledge:
- A "variant record" is a unit of data that describes a genetic variation in a DNA sequence; 
- A "quality score" is a measure of the confidence in the accuracy of the variant record; 
- "VCF" stands for Variant Call Format, a standard file format for storing genetic variation data; 
- A "public VCF file" is one that is accessible to everyone, not restricted by access controls; 
- An "active user" is one whose account is currently enabled and allowed to interact with the system; 
- A "filter status" indicates whether a variant record has passed or failed a set of predefined checks.

sql:
SELECT COUNT(DISTINCT al.file_id) AS successful_file_count
FROM access_logs al
WHERE al.is_successful = 1;

SELECT COUNT(*) AS access_count
FROM access_logs
WHERE user_id = 1 AND action = 'download';

SELECT DISTINCT validated_by
FROM vcf_validation_logs
WHERE validated_by IS NOT NULL;
